{"type":"visualization","id":"data-persistence-guide","attributes":{"title":"DataPersistence guide","description":"Managed by shared-gitops-k8s-cluster","visState":"{\"title\":\"DataPersistence guide\",\"type\":\"markdown\",\"params\":{\"fontSize\":12,\"openLinksInNewTab\":false,\"markdown\":\"## DataPersistence \\u2014 Postgres primary + replicas, Redis\\n\\nTopology: Lifeguard `postgres-primary` + `postgres-replica-{0,1}` (no Pgpool). Exporter scrapes the primary Service; replica health is visible via `pg_stat_replication_*` streaming rows.\\n\\n[**Open metrics (all)**](/app/data-explorer/discover/#/?_g=(filters:!(),refreshInterval:(pause:!f,value:30000),time:(from:now-15m,to:now))&_a=(discover:(columns:!(time,name,value,serviceName,metric.attributes.platform_component,metric.attributes.server,metric.attributes.client_addr,metric.attributes.slot_name,metric.attributes.state,metric.attributes.datname,metric.attributes.consumer_namespace),interval:auto,sort:!(!(time,desc))),metadata:(indexPattern:shared-observability-metrics,view:discover))&_q=(filters:!(),query:(language:lucene,query:'%28name.keyword%3A%20%28%22pg_stat_database_numbackends%22%20OR%20%22pg_settings_max_connections%22%20OR%20%22pg_stat_activity_count%22%29%29%20OR%20%28name.keyword%3A%20%28%22pg_up%22%20OR%20%22pg_replication_is_replica%22%20OR%20%22pg_replication_lag_seconds%22%20OR%20%22pg_stat_replication_pg_wal_lsn_diff%22%29%29%20OR%20%28name.keyword%3A%20%22pg_database_size_bytes%22%29%20OR%20%28name.keyword%3A%20redis_*%29'))) \\u2014 Postgres + Redis gauges.\\n[**Open replication**](/app/data-explorer/discover/#/?_g=(filters:!(),refreshInterval:(pause:!f,value:30000),time:(from:now-15m,to:now))&_a=(discover:(columns:!(time,name,value,serviceName,metric.attributes.platform_component,metric.attributes.server,metric.attributes.client_addr,metric.attributes.slot_name,metric.attributes.state,metric.attributes.datname,metric.attributes.consumer_namespace),interval:auto,sort:!(!(time,desc))),metadata:(indexPattern:shared-observability-metrics,view:discover))&_q=(filters:!(),query:(language:lucene,query:'name.keyword%3A%20%28%22pg_up%22%20OR%20%22pg_replication_is_replica%22%20OR%20%22pg_replication_lag_seconds%22%20OR%20%22pg_stat_replication_pg_wal_lsn_diff%22%29'))) \\u2014 `pg_up`, is_replica, WAL lag bytes per standby.\\n[**Open Redis**](/app/data-explorer/discover/#/?_g=(filters:!(),refreshInterval:(pause:!f,value:30000),time:(from:now-15m,to:now))&_a=(discover:(columns:!(time,name,value,serviceName,metric.attributes.platform_component,metric.attributes.server,metric.attributes.client_addr,metric.attributes.slot_name,metric.attributes.state,metric.attributes.datname,metric.attributes.consumer_namespace),interval:auto,sort:!(!(time,desc))),metadata:(indexPattern:shared-observability-metrics,view:discover))&_q=(filters:!(),query:(language:lucene,query:'name.keyword%3A%20redis_*'))) \\u2014 clients, memory, keyspace.\\n\\n### What to watch\\n1. **`pg_up`** \\u2014 exporter scrape of primary = 1\\n2. **`pg_replication_is_replica`** \\u2014 primary scrape should stay **0**\\n3. **Streaming replicas** \\u2014 two `client_addr` rows in `pg_stat_replication_pg_wal_lsn_diff`, state `streaming`, lag \\u2248 0\\n4. **DB backends** \\u2014 `pg_stat_database_numbackends` by `datname`\\n5. **Redis** \\u2014 connected clients + memory used\\n\\n### Saved searches (Discover \\u2192 Open)\\n- **DataPersistence / Platform metrics**\\n- **DataPersistence / Postgres connections**\\n- **DataPersistence / Replication**\\n- **DataPersistence / Redis**\\n- **DataPersistence / DB pressure logs** (log index)\\n\\nScraped via OTel `prometheus/data` \\u2192 `postgres-exporter:9187` + `redis-metrics` \\u2192 Data Prepper \\u2192 `otel-v1-apm-metrics*`. Managed by shared-gitops-k8s-cluster.\"},\"aggs\":[]}","uiStateJSON":"{}","kibanaSavedObjectMeta":{"searchSourceJSON":"{\"query\":{\"query\":\"\",\"language\":\"lucene\"},\"filter\":[]}"}},"references":[]}
